-- Pettitte Will Attempt Comeback With Yankees, YES Network Says
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-03-16T16:48:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/pettitte-will-attempt-comeback-with-yankees-yes-network-says.html
Andy Pettitte  will attempt a
comeback and has signed a minor-league contract with the  New
York Yankees , the Yankees Entertainment & Sports Network
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The 39-year-old lefthanded pitcher helped the
Yankees win five World Series championships in 13 seasons and
has a record 19 postseason victories.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jay Beberman in New York at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mason Levinson at 
 mlevinson@bloomberg.net  